{"questionId":"6179","questionHtml":"<p>Beryllium-10 is used to investigate ice samples from Antarctica. A sample of ice initially contains 7.6 × 10<sup>11</sup> atoms of beryllium-10. The present activity of the sample is 8.0 × 10<sup>−3</sup> Bq.</p>\n<p>Determine, in years, the age of the sample.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>λ</em>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{\\ln 2}}{{1.4 \\times {{10}^6}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>ln</mi>\n      <mo>⁡</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.4</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>6</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong> = 4.95&nbsp;× 10<sup>–7</sup>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>y<sup>–1</sup><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>rearranging of&nbsp;<em>A</em> =&nbsp;<em>λN</em><sub>0</sub>e<sup>–<em>λt</em></sup> to give –<em>λt</em> = ln&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{8.0 \\times {{10}^{-3}} \\times 365 \\times 24 \\times 60 \\times 60}}{{4.95 \\times {{10}^{-7}} \\times 7.6 \\times {{10}^{11}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>8.0</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>365</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>24</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>60</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>60</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4.95</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>7</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>7.6</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>11</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>=&nbsp;–0.400<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><em>t</em> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{ - 0.400}}{{ - 4.95 \\times {{10}^{ - 7}}}} = 8.1 \\times {10^5}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>0.400</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>4.95</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>7</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>8.1</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>y<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Allow ECF from MP1</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"6179","referenceCode":"18M.2.HL.TZ1.6b.iii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Beryllium-10 is used to investigate ice samples from Antarctica. A sample of ice initially contains 7.6 × 1011 atoms of beryllium-10. The present activity of the sample is 8.0 × 10","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 12: Quantum and nuclear physics","12.2 – Nuclear physics","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 12: Quantum and nuclear physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}